396
00:32:52,503 --> 00:32:55,700
Thou wilt not confess
to heresy,

397
00:32:55,773 --> 00:32:59,607
to having lain
with Satan himself.

398
00:33:00,812 --> 00:33:02,905
If that be thy contention,

399
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,108
then it shall be done

400
00:33:05,183 --> 00:33:07,083
that no man among us

401
00:33:07,151 --> 00:33:09,415
shall yet covet thee again.

402
00:33:09,487 --> 00:33:11,478
No man's loins

403
00:33:11,556 --> 00:33:14,719
shall yet be stirred
by thy countenance.

404
00:33:24,402 --> 00:33:26,996
Mary Worth,

405
00:33:27,071 --> 00:33:30,370
when the last of us
hath made his mark,

406
00:33:30,441 --> 00:33:33,467
if thou hast not confessed,

407
00:33:33,544 --> 00:33:37,071
thou shalt be excommunicated
from the church

408
00:33:37,148 --> 00:33:39,844
and left to die.

409
00:33:48,259 --> 00:33:51,626
"The local magistrate felt
the mirror was a just punishment

410
00:33:51,696 --> 00:33:54,893
to remind her that vanity
was the ultimate sin

411
00:33:54,966 --> 00:33:57,127
for her unwillingness
to confess."

412
00:34:17,455 --> 00:34:20,117
"Mary stared into the mirror

413
00:34:20,191 --> 00:34:22,557
and begged whomever lies
within it to take her.

414
00:34:22,627 --> 00:34:24,959
She then cursed the town
and all its people

415
00:34:25,029 --> 00:34:26,587
and vowed to have
her revenge."

416
00:34:45,416 --> 00:34:48,510
"One of the townspeople
that was present

417
00:34:48,586 --> 00:34:51,020
during the execution
was quoted in saying,

418
00:34:51,089 --> 00:34:54,058
